        <h2>Courses</h2>
        <div class="course">
            <h3>Project Design Thinking in Enterprise and Prototyping</h3>
            <p>Design Thinking is a user-centered approach to solving complex problems and fostering innovation in enterprise environments. Prototyping is a crucial phase within Design Thinking, allowing teams to create tangible solutions for iterative testing and refinement.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Empathy: Understanding user needs and experiences.</li>
                <li>Ideation: Generating a broad range of ideas.</li>
                <li>Prototyping: Creating models to explore solutions.</li>
                <li>Testing: Gathering feedback to refine prototypes.</li>
                <li>Implementation: Scaling solutions into the enterprise.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="course">
            <h3>Project Design and Planning (BPM210)</h3>
            <p>This course covers how to initiate, plan, execute, and close projects effectively, including scope, time, cost, and risk management.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Project Lifecycle: Initiation, Planning, Execution, Monitoring, and Closure.</li>
                <li>Scope Management: Defining and controlling the project scope.</li>
                <li>Time Management: Developing schedules and timelines.</li>
                <li>Cost Management: Budgeting and managing project costs.</li>
                <li>Risk Management: Identifying and responding to risks.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="course">
            <h3>Legal and Ethical Issues in Projects (BPM211)</h3>
            <p>This course examines the legal frameworks and ethical considerations essential for managing projects, including contracts, compliance, and stakeholder rights.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Contracts and Agreements: Understanding project contracts.</li>
                <li>Intellectual Property (IP): Protecting creations and designs.</li>
                <li>Compliance: Adhering to legal regulations.</li>
                <li>Ethical Decision-Making: Navigating moral dilemmas.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="course">
            <h3>Principles of Marketing for Project Managers (BPM213)</h3>
            <p>This course integrates marketing principles into project management, focusing on market research, branding, and communication strategies.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Market Research: Understanding market needs.</li>
                <li>Marketing Mix (4Ps): Product, Price, Place, and Promotion.</li>
                <li>Target Audience: Identifying and reaching the right customers.</li>
                <li>Brand Management: Creating a strong brand image.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="course">
            <h3>Creativity and Innovation in Projects (BPM214)</h3>
            <p>This course explores how creativity and innovation drive success in project management, including brainstorming, disruptive innovation, and change management.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Creativity Techniques: Brainstorming and mind mapping.</li>
                <li>Innovation Process: From idea generation to implementation.</li>
                <li>Disruptive Innovation: Creating products that alter markets.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

